450,IssuesEvent,2016-01-11 21:40:49+00:00,12848640,paulgb/runipy,3019665,jakirkham,,,opened,Add a check for notebooks running via runipy,[],[],0,"The goal of `runipy` is to batch notebook(s) and so is clearly decoupled from interactivity. However, there is a strong desire to have interactive components in notebooks.

Initial independent attempts of my own included monkey patch mocked out portions of interactive components in my own use of `runipy`. However, these are many and varied and it is simply not reasonable to hope to get all of these.

The best thing I can think of in these cases is to provide some way for the notebook to detect it is running in batch like setting a variable say `__RUNIPY__`.

When this variable is present, it can represent the notebook is being run in batch. Users can then check for this variable and use it as a guard thus blocking any interactive elements from running.

Perhaps, with other changes, we may be able to gain support for some subset of the interactive elements that are non-blocking. At present, I think it is just more straightforward to encourage users to skip interactive elements when running via `runipy` and possibly output relevant results so that they can generate the interactive elements later when they are running interactively.",{},{}
