1357,IssuesEvent,2018-01-19 07:25:59+00:00,4690111,nikipore/stompest,718092,arjunv,,,opened,receiveFrame does not accept a timeout parameter ,[],[],0,"Currently the synchronous version of stompest do not accept a timeout paramter to the [method `receiveFrame()`](https://github.com/nikipore/stompest/blob/master/src/core/stompest/sync/client.py#L343). While one could use the [method `canRead()`](https://github.com/nikipore/stompest/blob/master/src/core/stompest/sync/client.py#L307) in a queue with a single consumer, this will still cause the cause execution to be indefinitely blocked, should another consumer fetch a frame in between the calls to `canRead` and `receiveFrame`. Notably, both the methods `connect()` and `canRead()` accepts a `timeout` parameter, while neither are extremely blocking in nature.",{},{}
