        size=size or '',
    )

should do the trick.",{},{}
3181,IssuesEvent,2015-01-20 03:51:17+00:00,28750286,nedbat/django_coverage_plugin,23789,nedbat,,,closed,Crash on non-file templates,[],[],1,"Thanks for writing this, Ned. I think it's a great idea and a very useful tool to have. So I get to file the first issue on it ;)

django-coverage-plugin crashes on templates that don't have an underlying file. For example, this view:

    from django.template import Template, Context
    from django.http import HttpResponse


    def i_am_broken(request):
        tpl = Template(u""Hello!"")
        return HttpResponse(tpl.render(Context({})))

And this test:
```
from django.test import TestCase


class MyTest(TestCase):

