3198,IssuesEvent,2016-04-04 16:47:09+00:00,1576129,KristianOellegaard/django-hvad,1564463,nuarhu,,,closed,"Error: ""Wrong Manager"" from template when accessing get_translation_aware_manager result",[],[],2,"Hi!

I've just reactivated an old project that was using an old version with Django 1.6.7, Django CMS 3.0.5 and Django Hvad 0.4.1.

After upgrading all components, my codebase now uses: Django 1.9.4, CMS 3.2.3, and Hvad 1.5.0.

After changing some issues with the admin I'm now facing a problem when adding context data to my templates that fetch a list of regular Django models that have foreign key relations to TranslatableModels.

Basically, the queryset that I add to the context is created using `get_translation_aware_manager(models.KnowledgeElement).language()`.

`KnowledgeElement` is a regular Django model that defines custom CMS placeholders and has foreignkey relations to the TranslatableModels `OperatingLevel` and `Topic`.

```
class KnowledgeElement(KnowbasePage):
    operating_level = models.ForeignKey(OperatingLevel, null=False, related_name=""%(class)s_related"",
                                        verbose_name=_(""Handlungsebene""))
    topic = models.ForeignKey(Topic, null=False, related_name=""%(class)s_related"", verbose_name=_(""Thema""))
```

Both `OperatingLevel` and `Topic` derive from the same abstract model and that abstract model defines the following translations:

```
class ClassificationModel(TranslatableModel):
    translations = TranslatedFields(
        name=models.CharField(_('Name'), max_length=255), null=True, blank=True,
        slug=models.SlugField(_('Slug'), max_length=255, null=True, blank=True,
                              help_text=_('Wird automatisch aus dem Namen generiert und ist Teil der URL. Sollte nur '
                                          'überschrieben werden, wenn die URL zu lang werden würde.')),
    )

    class Meta:
        abstract = True
        ordering = ('name',)
        unique_together = (('name', 'language_code'), ('slug', 'language_code'))
```

When I add the following to my template context:

    def get_context_data(self, **kwargs):
        kwargs['placeholder_language'] = get_language() or settings.LANGUAGES[0][0]
        kwargs['related_objects'] = get_translation_aware_manager(models.KnowledgeElement).language().filter(operating_level=self.oplevel).all()
        return super().get_context_data(**kwargs)

The following template code throws the error:

```
{% block navigation %}

{% if related_objects %}    <------------------ throws WrongManager
    <div class=""navigation"">

        <h2>{% blocktrans with name=object.name %}
            Themen in der Rubrik {{ name }}:
        {% endblocktrans %}</h2>

        <ul>
        {% for kel in related_objects|dictsort:""topic.name"" %}
            <li><a href=""{{ kel.get_absolute_url }}"">{{ kel.topic.name }}</a></li>
        {% endfor %}
        </ul>
    </div>
{% endif %}

{% endblock %}
```

The error is:

> Internal Server Error: /kbase/oplevel/betriebsvereinbarungen
> Traceback (most recent call last):
>   File ""venv/lib/python3.4/site-packages/django/db/models/options.py"", line 580, in get_field
>     return self.fields_map[field_name]
> KeyError: 'name'
> 
> During handling of the above exception, another exception occurred:
> 
> 
> Traceback (most recent call last):
>   File ""venv/lib/python3.4/site-packages/hvad/utils.py"", line 126, in __call__
>     return self.real(name, *args, **kwargs)
>   File ""venv/lib/python3.4/site-packages/django/db/models/options.py"", line 582, in get_field
>     raise FieldDoesNotExist('%s has no field named %r' % (self.object_name, field_name))
> django.core.exceptions.FieldDoesNotExist: Topic has no field named 'name'

Certainly, `Topic` has no field `name`, only a translated field of that name. I'm completely at a loss. I've tried several things like removing lines from the template but it all ends up with that error. It actually makes no difference whether I add the `get_translation_aware_manager` or not so I'm not sure I've done it correct at all. The documentation and StackOverflow have not been of any help so far.

This template and view code was working without the `get_translation_aware_manager` with the old version, so it should be possible to get it to work?",{},{}
