`{""id"":""job3"",""func"": ""jobs:job1"",""args"":""11"",""trigger"":""interval"",""seconds"":10}`
return
```
{
    ""id"": ""job3"",
    ""name"": ""job3"",
    ""func"": ""jobs:job1"",
    ""args"": [
        ""1"",
        ""1""
    ],
    ""kwargs"": {},
    ""trigger"": ""interval"",
    ""start_date"": ""2018-05-02T16:54:43.103900+08:00"",
    ""seconds"": 10,
    ""misfire_grace_time"": 1,
    ""max_instances"": 1,
    ""next_run_time"": ""2018-05-02T16:54:43.103900+08:00""
}
```

args --> Iterate 11 to 1，1

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
post 
`{""id"":""job3"",""func"": ""jobs:job1"",""args"":""(11,22)"",""trigger"":""interval"",""seconds"":10}`

result 
```
{
    ""error_message"": ""The list of positional arguments is longer than the target callable can handle (allowed: 2, given in args: 7)""
}
```

---------------------------------------------------------------------------
flask_apscheduler\api.py  
 Line 38
` data = request.get_json(force=True)`

ex:
Add a row
`print(data,type((data['args'])))`
output
`{'id': 'job3', 'func': 'jobs:job1', 'args': '(11,22)', 'trigger': 'interval', 'seconds': 10} <class 'str'>`

apscheduler\schedulers\base.py

Line412
```
        job_kwargs = {
            'trigger': self._create_trigger(trigger, trigger_args),
            'executor': executor,
            'func': func,
            'args': tuple(args) if args is not None else (),
            'kwargs': dict(kwargs) if kwargs is not None else {},
            'id': id,
            'name': name,
            'misfire_grace_time': misfire_grace_time,
            'coalesce': coalesce,
            'max_instances': max_instances,
            'next_run_time': next_run_time
