3592,IssuesEvent,2016-05-08 14:08:22+00:00,33884891,apache/incubator-airflow,4282712,bolkedebruin,47359,apache,closed,[Question] How to deploy DAGs in a production environment without human intervention,[],[],3,"Hi all,

I wonder if any of you guys, that are more experienced using the platform, is working with a CD approach.

My idea is develop an automatic process that deploys new DAGs. The problems arise when you have to manually add variables and connections in the metadata DB. Have some of you tackled this problem?

Maybe a workaround could be implementing a feature so when you run the initdb command you can pass a file where your connection or variables used by your DAGs are explicited. For example like this: `airflow initdb --conections connections.yml`.

Another option could be scripting the DMLs outside airflow and incorporating into the automatic deployment process before deploying the DAGs, but I think using the defined models in the platform is a better solution.

I would love to know your thoughts about this topic.

Thanks in advance!",{},{}
