3926,IssuesEvent,2016-09-17 03:41:03+00:00,14993021,ipython/traitlets,4041990,rmorshea,230453,ipython,opened,Instance trait type default value confusion,[],[],0,"We raise here:

```python
class A(HasTraits):
	inst = Instance(Foo)

A().inst
```

But not here:

```python
class A(HasTraits):
	inst = Instance(Foo, allow_none=True)

A().inst
```

These seems magical, and is not at all implied by `allow_none=True`.

It seems like we should try to enforce this convention:

```python
class A(HasTraits):
	inst = Instance(Foo, default_value=None, allow_none=True)

A().inst
```

Or at the very least:

set `allow_none=True` if `default_value=None`

```python
class A(HasTraits):
	inst = Instance(Foo, default_value=None)

A().inst
```",{},{}
