4227,IssuesEvent,2016-07-25 16:01:58+00:00,1126087,gitpython-developers/GitPython,1854968,kylepjohnson,503709,gitpython-developers,opened,_io.BufferedWriter in cmd.py,[],[],0,"I'm getting the following error my unit tests (Python 3.5.2; GitPython 2.0.7):

``` python
/Users/kyle/cltk/venv/lib/python3.5/site-packages/git/cmd.py:622: ResourceWarning: unclosed file <_io.BufferedWriter name='/dev/null'>
  **subprocess_kwargs
```

An unclosed handle isn't a big deal, however it clutters up my output. This error comes out of [this try/except in cmd.py](https://github.com/gitpython-developers/GitPython/blob/dc2ec79a88a787f586df8c40ed0fd6657dce31dd/git/cmd.py#L611).

I know there are a few ways to solve this (`with`, a new `except`, changing `stderr` and `stdout` paramters) and don't know what you'd prefer. If it helps, here's how IPython fixed this a few years back: <https://github.com/ipython/ipython/pull/5222/files>.

If you think this would be a fairly easy fix, let me know and I volunteer myself.

Thanks for this excellent package! My project uses it extensively.",{},{}
