4533,IssuesEvent,2018-06-19 18:04:05+00:00,14448779,astropy/astropy-helpers,11289391,StanczakDominik,847984,astropy,opened,${packagename}/,[],[],0,"Hi there! I'm not sure this is in astropy-helpers scope, but here goes.

Over at PlasmaPy we were trying to solve PlasmaPy/PlasmaPy#495. To summarize: we transitioned from running tests via `pytest plasmapy` with `pytest-cov` with `.coveragerc` located in our repository's root, to running `python setup.py test --coverage` via `astropy_helpers` (which we were using, but we weren't aware of that awesome functionality). This errored unless our coveragerc file was in `plasmapy/tests/coveragerc`, which is AFAIK how `astropy` does it right now. However, coveragepy stopped detecting `.coveragerc` settings unless it was in the repository root.
 
* PlasmaPy/PlasmaPy#497 tried to add `[run] source` to `.coveragerc`. That failed.
* PlasmaPy/PlasmaPy#502 is what we went with for now, with full knowledge of an ugly hack - keeping an empty file `plasmapy/test/coveragerc` so `python setup.py test --coverage` doesn't fail the check, and using `.coveragerc` in the repo root (because that ended up working, believe it or not). 
* PlasmaPy/PlasmaPy#496 tried using a link to the `.coveragerc` file, but I couldn't get it working with packaging.",{},{}
4534,IssuesEvent,2018-02-02 14:43:17+00:00,73024951,astropy/sphinx-automodapi,314716,astrofrog,847984,astropy,closed,Enable parallel building,[],[],1,"If I try and run sphinx in parallel I get:

