5270,IssuesEvent,2017-12-22 13:50:31+00:00,38744670,zalando/patroni,339913,alexeyklyukin,1564818,zalando,opened,Allow manual failovers when master is not present,[],[],0,"At the moment, when master is not present and the replicas cannot promote themselves for some reason (i.e. being to far from the last known master position) there is no way to force the promotion of one of the replicas. We can introduce the `failover` command that does exactly this (checking that the master is not present), and rename our existing command that does the controlled switchover when the master is present to `switchover`.

This would also address https://github.com/zalando/patroni/issues/520",{},{}
5285,IssuesEvent,2017-03-21 17:16:15+00:00,35882519,zalando/connexion,238933,vimalloc,1564818,zalando,opened,Splitting swagger files error,[],[],0,"### Description
When attempting to split a large swagger configuration file into smaller modular parts I am getting a ```SwaggerValidationError```

See:
* https://github.com/OAI/OpenAPI-Specification/blob/master/guidelines/REUSE.md
* https://apihandyman.io/writing-openapi-swagger-specification-tutorial-part-8-splitting-specification-file/

### Expected behaviour
Breaking swagger configurations into smaller files and referencing them should not produce an error

 ```
$ref: 'filename.yaml/#Reference'
```

### Actual behaviour
The references to other files raises this error:
 ``` 
swagger_spec_validator.common.SwaggerValidationError: unknown url type: 'filename.yaml/'
```


### Steps to reproduce
test.yaml
```yaml
swagger: ""2.0""

info:
  title: ""Test""
  version: ""1.0""

basePath: /v1.0

produces:
  - application/json

consumes:
  - application/json

paths:
  /foo:
    get:
      operationId: test.foo
      responses:
        200:
          description: Foo
          schema:
            $ref: 'foo.yaml/#Foo'
```

foo.yaml
```yaml
Foo:
  description: Test foo
  type: object
  required:
    - foo
  properties:
    foo:
      type: string
      example: 'foo'
```

test.py:
```python
#!/usr/bin/env python3
import connexion
app = connexion.App(__name__, 9091)

def foo():
    return {'foo': 'bar'}

if __name__ == '__main__':
    app.add_api('test.yaml', validate_responses=True, strict_validation=True)
    app.run()
```


### Additional info:
Python 3.6.0
Conexion Version: 1.1.5
",{},{}
