5324,IssuesEvent,2018-08-08 10:02:31+00:00,22877727,irods/python-irodsclient,11211145,mikkonie,1790166,irods,opened,Filter chaining in queries not working as expected for multiple criteria on the same column,[],[],0,"I was in need to do a query on the ICAT database for data objects within a certain collection, where the name of the data object would contain ""XXX"" and would NOT contain ""YYY"". I tried to achieve this with the following query:

```
session.query(DataObject).filter(
    Criterion('like', DataObject.path, '%/some/path')).filter(
        Criterion('like', DataObject.name, '%XXX%')).filter(
            Criterion('not like', DataObject.name, '%YYY%'))
```

Expected outcome: Returning DataObjects under the path with name containing ""XXX"" but not containing ""YYY""

Actual outcome: Returns all DataObjects under the path which don't contain ""YYY"". The filter for ""like %XXX%"" is not applied.

In this case, only the first and last filters get applied to the query. If I reverse the order of the last two filters, again the middle one gets omitted. It seems that if there are multiple filters on the same column, only the last one of them affects the query.

Now, this might not be the most optimal way to do this query. I in fact solved the issue on my end by instead doing a raw SQL query using SpecificQuery. But I thought this was still worth reporting.",{},{}
