    p = PipelineA()
    p.start(queue_name=""mapreduceQueue"")

The idea is that once the `MapperPipeline` in `PipelineA` is done, process its output in `PipelineB`. The output I care about here is the `mapreduce_id`(or `job_id`) of the `MapperPipeline`, but the default output is a list of filenames produced by the mapper. More details can be found in this [source line](https://github.com/GoogleCloudPlatform/appengine-mapreduce/blob/master/python/src/mapreduce/mapper_pipeline.py#L46). 

## Question
How can I let the `MapperPipeline` return its `mapreduce_id`?",{},{}
