5804,IssuesEvent,2016-05-12 22:27:01+00:00,7209075,pantsbuild/pants,157586,jsirois,3065172,pantsbuild,closed,`./pants roots` does not respect `source` scope options.,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/pantsbuild/pants/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'fc2929'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/pantsbuild/pants/labels/in-progress', 'name': 'in-progress', 'color': '009800'}]",[],2,"As found in #3417 and demonstratable in https://github.com/pantsbuild/issues-3417, [custom source root configuration](https://github.com/pantsbuild/issues-3417/blob/master/pants.ini#L13-L19) like so:
```ini
[source]
# TODO(John Sirois): Eliminate these hand-specified roots once this issue is resolved:
#  https://github.com/pantsbuild/pants/issues/2483
source_roots: {
    '3rdparty/go': ['go_remote'],
    'src/go/src': ['go']
  }
```

Works:
```
$ ./pants options | grep source_roots
source.source_roots = {u'src/go/src': [u'go'], u'3rdparty/go': [u'go_remote']} (from CONFIG in pants.ini)
```

But `./pants roots` does not see this:
```
$ ./pants roots
src/go: go
3rdparty/go: go_remote
```
The reported `src/go` `go` root is actually configured to be `src/go/src`.

",{},{}
5813,IssuesEvent,2017-04-10 21:52:59+00:00,7209075,pantsbuild/pants,46740,stuhood,3065172,pantsbuild,closed,pants.backend.codegen dependency tree should be inverted,"[{'id': 22426648, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/pantsbuild/pants/labels/enhancement', 'name': 'enhancement', 'color': '84b6eb', 'default': True}]",[],1,"Right now pants.backend.codegen depends upon pants.backend.jvm and pants.backend.python.  This should be the other way around.  Each pants.backend.<language> that wants to provide code generation for its language should depend upon a common set of tooling/APIs provided by pants.backend.codegen.
",{},{}
5867,IssuesEvent,2015-10-21 21:21:30+00:00,7695747,wal-e/wal-e,7191,fdr,3310438,wal-e,closed,PostgreSQL 8.4 doesn't support 'wal_level' setting,[],[],3,"I've just finished setting up wal-e for a postgreSQL 8.4.22 instance (on Ubuntu Linux).

When I restarted my database after adding the suggested config values I got this error.

    FATAL:  unrecognized configuration parameter ""wal_level""

I commented out that line and restarted my database - it is now running fine and writing files to my S3 bucket.
However, I'm not sure if it's actually doing the right thing.
How can I tell if it's working correctly?

The [docs for 9.0](http://www.postgresql.org/docs/9.0/static/runtime-config-wal.html) say:

    The default value is minimal...
    But minimal WAL does not contain enough information to reconstruct the data from a base backup and the WAL logs, so either archive or hot_standby level must be used to enable WAL archiving (archive_mode) and streaming replication.

I can't seem to find out what the default behaviour is on 8.4.",{},{}
