6007,IssuesEvent,2015-07-15 10:08:21+00:00,9322649,html5lib/html5lib-python,239510,JulienPalard,4092973,html5lib,opened,"Warning about ""Coercing non-XML name"" when name contains a column "":"".",[],[],0,"As: `nonXmlNameBMPRegexp` is defined by `re.compile('[\x00-,/:-@`... (note the column).

[In ihatexml.py, at line 260](https://github.com/html5lib/html5lib-python/blob/master/html5lib/ihatexml.py#L260):
```
replaceChars = set(nonXmlNameBMPRegexp.findall(nameRest))
for char in replaceChars:
    warnings.warn(""Coercing non-XML name {}"".format(name), DataLossWarning)
```
if a char in a name is in `nonXmlNameBMPRegexp`, like `:`, a Warning is triggered, yet, as far as I searched, `:` is allowed for namespace purpose and by definition in the [XML 1.1 spec](http://www.w3.org/TR/xml11/):

> [Definition: A Name is a token beginning with a letter or one of a few punctuation characters, and
> continuing with letters, digits, hyphens, underscores, colons, or full stops, together known as name
> characters.] Names beginning with the string ""xml"", or with any string which would match (('X'|'x')
> ('M'|'m') ('L'|'l')), are reserved for standardization in this or future versions of this specification.

Did I missed something obvious here or is this a bug ?",{},{}
6035,IssuesEvent,2015-04-24 20:10:54+00:00,19079404,thefactory/marathon-python,53127,mbabineau,4227819,thefactory,closed,Urgent BUG: to_json() is returning unexpected result under python3 version,[],[],3,"In a nutshell, under python3 version, we should replace ``iteritems`` with ``items`` in file https://github.com/thefactory/marathon-python/blob/master/marathon/util.py. I saw that you forgot to change ``hasattr(obj, 'iteritems')`` to ``hasattr(obj, 'items')``.",{},{}
6036,IssuesEvent,2015-11-04 23:31:56+00:00,42324225,lyft/confidant,134241,woodrow,4269340,lyft,opened,Confidant web interface should indicate if USE_ENCRYPTION=False,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/lyft/confidant/labels/easy', 'name': 'easy', 'color': '009800'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/lyft/confidant/labels/enhancement', 'name': 'enhancement', 'color': '84b6eb'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/lyft/confidant/labels/frontend', 'name': 'frontend', 'color': '5319e7'}]",[],0,"We should show a warning header/banner if you've intentionally disabled encryption (for e.g. in development or trying out Confidant via Docker).

