This is motivated by the notodiff tool which is part of https://github.com/googlei18n/nototools.

Here's the sample output produced when I compared NotoSansSymbols2-Regular.ttf generated by the pipeline (A mentioned below) and the generated by the Glyphs.app (B mentioned below) from the same source in noto-source/src/NotoSansSymbols2-Regular.glyphs:
""....
  in A but not B: ['nonmarkingreturn', 'null', 'space', 'uni1018B', 'uni1018C', 'uni1018D', 'uni1018E', 'uni10190', 'uni10191', 'uni10192', 'uni10193', 'uni10194', 'uni10195', 'uni10196', 'uni10197', 'uni10198', 'uni10199', 'uni1019A', 'uni1019B', 'uni101A0', 'uni101D0', 'uni101D1', 'uni101D2', 'uni101D3', 'uni101D4', 'uni101D5', 'uni101D6', 'uni101D7', 'uni101D8', 'uni101D9', 'uni101DA', 'uni101DB', 'uni101DC', 'uni101DD', 'uni101DE', 'uni101DF', 'uni101E0', 'uni
....
  in B but not A: ['u1018B', 'u1018C', 'u1018D', 'u1018E', 'u10190', 'u10191', 'u10192', 'u10193', 'u10194', 'u10195', 'u10196', 'u10197', 'u10198', 'u10199', 'u1019A', 'u1019B', 'u101A0', 'u101D0', 'u101D1', 'u101D2', 'u101D3', 'u101D4', 'u101D5', 'u101D6', 'u101D7', 'u101D8', 'u101D9', 'u101DA', 'u101DB', 'u101DC', 'u101DD', 'u101DE', 'u101DF', 'u.....
""
You can notice that uni1018B in A corresponds to u1018B in B, uni1018D in A corresponds to u1018D in B, etc... However notodiff doesn't notice this...

I could add an option to notodiff (e.g., --try-matching-harder) that would retrieve the last 4 or 5 hex digits in the name and use this as a key to the name matching, but I  wanted to understand if we could make some changes in the font generation tools.


