6465,IssuesEvent,2017-11-07 19:55:48+00:00,6235174,conda/conda,15839840,tomashek,6392739,conda,closed,"test.py error ""prefix is not writeable"" ",[],[],6,"While attempting to use ""pyinstaller"" to create a standalone conda-index executable, the resulting binary failed in “conda/gateways/disk/test.py” prefix_is_writable because that method assumes the prefix is a python root directory, and in the case of the standalone, the “prefix” is the executable’s current directory. If I add append sys.executable to the end of the “find_first_existing” call parameter list, then it worked as expected.

Of course, this particular writability check seems unnecessary for conda-index, because the only writing is to the target, not the conda-meta directory.

Any change that would allow the creation of a standalone conda-index is appreciated.",{},{}
