6500,IssuesEvent,2018-04-19 05:39:51+00:00,6235174,conda/conda,1418419,kalefranz,6392739,conda,closed,Give more control over activated prompt,"[{'id': 413890457, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/conda/conda/labels/source:cio', 'name': 'source:cio', 'color': 'c2e0c6', 'default': False}, {'id': 865679648, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/conda/conda/labels/tag:shell', 'name': 'tag:shell', 'color': 'f4c5f9', 'default': False}, {'id': 16544532, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/conda/conda/labels/type:feature', 'name': 'type:feature', 'color': 'e99695', 'default': False}]",[],3,"From #2744 

We should add code to the prompt setting logic to let people customize this more with condarc. Similar to `config.changeps1`, but giving even more control.

---

I've got to say I'm not fond of the double either. Or the extra added space.  Prompts should be as short as possible for the screen real estate, and we've added three extra characters that probably aren't necessary.

I _would_ like to disambiguate from virtualenv, because someday conda envs and virtualenv **will** play nice together.

How about angle brackets?  `<ana40py35>ijstokes@petawawa:~%`
