6566,IssuesEvent,2017-03-08 07:37:48+00:00,12024604,OpenCobolIDE/OpenCobolIDE,6699539,GitMensch,6609701,OpenCobolIDE,opened,[BUG] displaying runtime configuation does not work with recent versions of `cobcrun` (`--runtime-conf` vs. `--runtime-env`),[],[],0,"Follow-Up to #215 

GitMensch:

For displaying the runtime configuration OCIDE calls `cobcrun -runtime-env`.
-runtime-env` was added to the development version of GnuCOBOL in 2015 and was renamed to `-runtime-conf` shortly after the implementation in OCIDE  - **before 2.0 rc1**, the first 2.0 version that was an official pre-release and the first version that shipped as a MinGW package along OCIDE.

I personally would simply replace `runtime-env` by `runtime-conf` - while ***old* development snapshots** don't have this and this it is documented in OCIDE already as ""Note that this command is supported only by recent builds of GnuCOBOL"". The other possibility to fix this is to use the less descriptive short option which wasn't and will not be changed: `cobcrun -r`.",{},{}
