7745,IssuesEvent,2018-03-16 18:24:40+00:00,32944298,Z3Prover/z3,11914638,lupodellemontagne,11668813,Z3Prover,opened,Z3 python bindings - assert_and_track shows as an implies in sexpr(),[],[],0,"Dear all,
when using the last version of the python bindings. If I set a constraint with assert_and_track the print with solver.sexpr() shows a corresponding implies statement. This is a bit inconsistent with the behaviour that is seen when assumptions are used to check is the model is satisfiable. 

```
import z3

x = z3.BitVec('x', 32)
a = z3.BitVec('a', 32)
solver = z3.Solver()
solver.set(unsat_core=True)
d = z3.Bool('d')
solver.assert_and_track(x != a, d) #comment this line
#solver.add(z3.Implies(x + a,d))   #decomment this line
solver.add(x == a)
print solver.sexpr()  #the pretty print shows the same set of assertions in both cases
print solver.check(d)                 
print solver.check(z3.Not(d))  
```
Probably the pretty print should specify that assert_and_track is not actually creating an implies among the assertions. 

Best Regards,
Giuseppe",{},{}
