7780,IssuesEvent,2015-08-12 10:15:22+00:00,23924195,Lasagne/Lasagne,629706,f0k,11752110,Lasagne,closed,Allow (custom) recurrent layers to accept more than one feature dimension,[],[],1,"As noted by @f0k here https://github.com/Lasagne/Lasagne/pull/294/files#r35102212, currently all the recurrent layers, including the `CustomRecurrentLayer`, squash the input past the third dimension.  The `CustomRecurrentLayer` doesn't need to do that; it should be able to accept N-D inputs and have, e.g., convolutional layers for its input-to-hidden and hidden-to-hidden connections.  I addressed that here: https://github.com/craffel/nntools/commit/1b55bbe9d910b7bc117040286ae0e6bc22053262 but it needs to be updated.  If and when there are more custom recurrent layer types #357, those should also be able to handle more-than-one-feature-dimension input.",{},{}
7795,IssuesEvent,2017-10-17 17:43:01+00:00,70920962,PyFilesystem/pyfilesystem2,554369,willmcgugan,11898830,PyFilesystem,closed,open_fs(writeable=True) doesn't care about read-only filesystems,"[{'id': 461639387, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/PyFilesystem/pyfilesystem2/labels/enhancement', 'name': 'enhancement', 'color': '84b6eb', 'default': True}]",[],4,"Just noticed this quite important bug: when calling `fs.open_fs` with `writeable` set to `True` (which according to the doc requires the given FS or FS URL to be writeable), nothing happens even if the given FS or FS URL maps to a read-only filesystem. I tried rolling back to `2.0.2`, issue was also there.

Can be reproduced with
```python
>>> fs.open_fs(""/path/to/an/existing/file.zip"", writeable=True)
```

I think the registry should raise an error (`CreateFailed`, `ResourceReadOnly` ?) if the returned filesystem is read-only according to its metadata, but for now it relies on the individual openers doing their things (and since none of them actually care about the `writeable` keyword, it doesn't do anything)",{},{}
7810,IssuesEvent,2018-04-26 22:51:32+00:00,99273369,NeurodataWithoutBorders/pynwb,1179288,elyall,12140348,NeurodataWithoutBorders,opened,ophys.ImagingPlane.imaging_rate should be float for consistency,[],[],0,"Sampling frequencies are recorded in multiple locations. As far as I'm aware, in all but 1 of these locations it is referred to as ""rate"" and is specified as a float. 

In [ophys.ImagingPlane](http://pynwb.readthedocs.io/en/latest/pynwb.ophys.html?highlight=opticalchannel#pynwb.ophys.ImagingPlane) the sampling frequency is specified under ""imaging_rate"" as a string. 

I'd recommend changing the parameter name (""imaging_rate"" -> ""rate"") and datatype (str -> float) for consistency. ",{},{}
