7862,IssuesEvent,2018-02-06 01:21:57+00:00,37496521,nteract/nteract,6611546,theengineear,12401040,nteract,closed,Move desktop kernel's cleanup into epics (and out of reducers),"[{'id': 788397480, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/nteract/nteract/labels/app:desktop', 'name': 'app:desktop', 'color': 'd4c5f9', 'default': False}]",[],0,"While working on the nbextension I noticed probably the murkiest thing in the desktop app -- the restart, interrupt, and kill kernel logic all live inside reducers even though they're inherently asynchronous. The fix is pretty simple -- it's a bit more ritual around using epics for these, leaving room for us to do proper checking of the cleanup.",{},{}
