8153,IssuesEvent,2018-07-11 16:04:04+00:00,46374199,IntelRealSense/librealsense,6958867,dorodnic,14095512,IntelRealSense,closed,Over-exposure Artifacts in Depth,"[{'id': 831104526, 'node_id': 'MDU6TGFiZWw4MzExMDQ1MjY=', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/IntelRealSense/librealsense/labels/help%20wanted', 'name': 'help wanted', 'color': '008672', 'default': True}]","[{'login': 'RealSense-Customer-Engineering', 'id': 34384799, 'node_id': 'MDQ6VXNlcjM0Mzg0Nzk5', 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars0.githubusercontent.com/u/34384799?v=4', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/RealSense-Customer-Engineering', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/RealSense-Customer-Engineering', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/RealSense-Customer-Engineering/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/RealSense-Customer-Engineering/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/RealSense-Customer-Engineering/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/RealSense-Customer-Engineering/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/RealSense-Customer-Engineering/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/RealSense-Customer-Engineering/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/RealSense-Customer-Engineering/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/RealSense-Customer-Engineering/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/RealSense-Customer-Engineering/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",6,"| Required Info                         |                                                                |
|---------------------------------|------------------------------------------- |
| Camera Model                       | D400 | 
| Firmware Version                   | 5.9.11 | 
| Operating System & Version |   Win10 | 
| Platform                                 | PC |
| SDK Version                            |  2.11.1 | 

### Issue Description
We are currently working with the RS in depth and trying to understand best settings / best practices.

One thing we are running into is artifacts due to over-exposure in the IR image. Below video shows the effect.

Of course, over-exposure is a thing to avoid, but so is under-exposure (as it does come with poor density and higher noise in the depth, as pointed out in the white paper). Hence we'd generally prefer an over-exposed input over an under-exposed input -- if there was a way to get rid of the artifacts.

In another video below I show how the default-settings-AE (which tends to under-expose) performs against manual exposure. You can see a clearly elevated noise level and a sparser depth map with the under-exposing AE vs. the ME. 

The artifacts appear within the boundaries of clearly over-exposed areas. It seems that the depth engine is ""hallucinating"" fill-in depth values where there's really no signal. The result of the artifacts are ""bellys"" and ""dents"" in the depth. Very visible on flat walls.

**We wonder if there's a way to tell the DS5 that it should rather ignore these pixels with no signal, and not assign a depth value, as opposed to fill them in with bad values.**

The K1 and K2 thresholds seem to help with this, but they come at the expense of sparsity in the rest of the depth image. Even more so for the ""high accuracy"" preset.

Given that the over-exposure artifacts seem to be limited to areas in the IR image that are literally white and 0-gradient, I think that a fast host-sided filter could be implemented quickly within librealsense. Would this be feasible?

 [Video 1 (over-exposure artifacts)](https://vimeo.com/275823145)

 [Video 2 (AE vs ME)](https://vimeo.com/275823870)

",{},{}
