8201,IssuesEvent,2017-05-11 19:42:42+00:00,43852872,PulpQE/pulp-smash,6206134,werwty,14839747,PulpQE,opened,Testing headers option for alternate content source,[],[],0,"https://pulp.plan.io/issues/1282

1. Create alternate content source configuration
`vi /etc/pulp/content/sources/conf.d/test.conf`
```
[content-world]
enabled: 1
priority: 0
expires: 3d
name: Content World
type: yum
base_url: http://bizhang.fedorapeople.org/
paths: zoo/ \
       test
max_concurrent: 10
max_speed: 1000
headers: X-RHUI-ID=1234 \
               X-Csrf-Token=31415926535897
```

2. Validate that headers shows up when `pulp-admin content sources list` is ran
3. run `pulp-admin content sources refresh` while monitoring the network traffic. 
I'm using tcpflow for this: `sudo tcpflow -p -c -i eth0 port 80`

4. Update test.conf with invalid headers
```
headers: X-RHUI-ID1234
```

5. run  `pulp-admin content sources refresh`  and make sure `Unparsable` is raised in the systemd logs
Note that the cli will show Task Succeeded despite nothing being downloaded. From what I can see this is because the task is running with no content sources, since the alternate content source is designed to fail over to the original source. ",{},{}
