8645,IssuesEvent,2017-03-28 08:18:25+00:00,16865424,pimutils/vdirsyncer,837573,untitaker,17852924,pimutils,closed,Lock pair during sync,"[{'id': 336203794, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/pimutils/vdirsyncer/labels/in%20progress', 'name': 'in progress', 'color': 'ededed', 'default': False}, {'id': 309156170, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/pimutils/vdirsyncer/labels/mod:%20sync', 'name': 'mod: sync', 'color': '207de5', 'default': False}, {'id': 80748618, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/pimutils/vdirsyncer/labels/type:%20enhancement', 'name': 'type: enhancement', 'color': 'bfd4f2', 'default': False}]",[],3,"I erroneously filed this at first as https://github.com/pimutils/khal/issues/590.

I just noticed that I can accidentally run sync from cron and from the terminal at the same time. I have not actually produced a problem from this, but unless synchronous write access is part of the design (which I doubt), this is going to burn someone.

Please lock a collection while it's being processed. It'd be great if this could be done per-pair, rather than for the entire run.

This is quite possibly related to #462, but also not the same, I think.",{},{}
