8689,IssuesEvent,2016-09-26 22:14:12+00:00,26516210,certbot/certbot,1750103,schoen,17889013,certbot,opened,Nginx parser has trouble with existing TLS listener on 8443,[],[],0,"I'm not sure what the underlying problem is, but `certbot-compatibility-test -ai` doesn't like this sample configuration file from our corpus (which has an existing HTTPS listener on port 8443, and an HTTP listener on port 80 that generates a redirect to the HTTPS site).

```
upstream django_server_random6822.example.org {
    server unix:/srv/http/random7047/live/website.sock;
}

server {
    listen 8443;
    server_name random6822.example.org;

    ssl on;
    ssl_certificate       /etc/nginx/empty_cert.pem;
    ssl_certificate_key   /etc/nginx/key2.pem;

    location /media/ {
        alias /srv/http/random7047/live/dynamic/public/;
        expires 7d;
    }
    location /static/ {
        alias /srv/http/random7047/live/static_collected/;
        expires 7d;
    }

    location / {
        proxy_pass http://django_server_random6822.example.org;
        include          /etc/nginx/proxy_params;
    }

    access_log /var/log/access.log combined;
    error_log  /var/log/error.log;
}

server {
    listen 80;
    server_name random6822.example.org;

    rewrite ^/(.*) https://random6822.example.org:8443/$1;
}
```",{},{}
8693,IssuesEvent,2017-02-05 03:14:29+00:00,26516210,certbot/certbot,220205,jsha,17889013,certbot,opened,Check for matching VirtualHosts before registering account,[],[],0,"I recently tried to issue on a new host, and provided a hostname for which there was no VirtualHost. However, Certbot led me through the whole account creation process first. Not a big deal in general, but the problem is that, if account creation happens, Certbot will print the ""IMPORTANT NOTES"" section after running to completion. This obscures the more important ""Cannot find a VirtualHost"" error. It would probably be better to check for ability to perform the challenges before attempting registration.

```
./certbot-auto -d blocktogether.org -d www.blocktogether.org -w /data/blocktogether/current/static/ --nginx

... prompt for email address etc ...

Performing the following challenges:
tls-sni-01 challenge for blocktogether.org
tls-sni-01 challenge for www.blocktogether.org
Cleaning up challenges
Cannot find a VirtualHost matching domain www.blocktogether.org.

IMPORTANT NOTES:
 - If you lose your account credentials, you can recover through
   e-mails sent to XXXXXXX.
 - Your account credentials have been saved in your Certbot
   configuration directory at /etc/letsencrypt. You should make a
   secure backup of this folder now. This configuration directory will
   also contain certificates and private keys obtained by Certbot so
   making regular backups of this folder is ideal.
```",{},{}
