8710,IssuesEvent,2016-12-08 19:07:01+00:00,26516210,certbot/certbot,479213,pde,17889013,certbot,opened,Protect against accidental interactivity with new questions?,"[{'id': 493513299, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/certbot/certbot/labels/potential%20workflow%20regression', 'name': 'potential workflow regression', 'color': 'c95054', 'default': False}, {'id': 146954792, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/certbot/certbot/labels/question', 'name': 'question', 'color': 'cc317c', 'default': True}, {'id': 200596079, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/certbot/certbot/labels/ui%20/%20ux', 'name': 'ui / ux', 'color': '5319e7', 'default': False}]",[],0,"When we add new `IDisplay` questions that also have sensible defaults, we create potential workflow regressions for people who have scripted something without using/knowing about `-n`.  We could mitigate this by detecting the lack of an interactive terminal, and forcing `-n` in that case.  Would it be safe to do so?",{},{}
