9125,IssuesEvent,2018-03-24 16:41:17+00:00,48904888,Cog-Creators/Red-DiscordBot,18455011,Redjumpman,23690422,Cog-Creators,opened,[V3/Downloader] Difficulty reloading a cog with multiple modules. ,[],[],0,"Please be sure to read through other issues as well to make sure what you are suggesting/reporting has not already
been suggested/reported

### Type:

- [ ] Suggestion
- [x] Bug

### Brief description of the problem
Reloading a cog seems to only work with the main module. Auxiliary module changes do not appear to be reflected in the reload. Workaround involves doing a bot shutdown and starting the bot again.

### Expected behavior
The cog and all supporting modules in the folder are ""reloaded"" to reflect the changes.
### Actual behavior
Only changes made to the main cog are reflected in the main cog. Shutting down the bot and starting it again is the only way to see the changes.
### Steps to reproduce

1. Make a cog with 2 modules
2. Add in an reproducible error to the auxiliary module.
3. Test the error
4. Fix the error
5. Reload the cog
",{},{}
9126,IssuesEvent,2017-08-30 01:10:54+00:00,48904888,Cog-Creators/Red-DiscordBot,19295487,flapjax,23690422,Cog-Creators,opened,[V3 Config] Method to delete individual key:value pairs,[],[],0,"I came across a situation when I was working on v3 cogs where I wanted to delete a single key:value pair from a user's settings, rather than clear all of the user's settings. I think it would be useful to have a method for this! The workaround I have been using is to set the value to `None`, and just deal with that situation in my code, but deleting the key entirely has the benefit of reverting back to the default setting.",{},{}
9129,IssuesEvent,2018-06-06 19:06:54+00:00,48904888,Cog-Creators/Red-DiscordBot,3731082,tekulvw,23690422,Cog-Creators,closed,[V3] Automatic man page for redbot command,"[{'id': 593836458, 'node_id': 'MDU6TGFiZWw1OTM4MzY0NTg=', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/Cog-Creators/Red-DiscordBot/labels/V3', 'name': 'V3', 'color': '006b75', 'default': False}]",[],7,"### Type:

- [x] Suggestion
- [ ] Bug

Since you have the `--help` flag which shows all flags for the `redbot` command, why not making a man page for that command, since a lot of users, as me, check man instead of `--help`. That can be automatically generated using `help2man`, which requires a `--help` flag and a `--version` flag (see #1479).
That can be probably made easily and included to the code, but before starting the PR, @tekulvw said it would be better to create an issue first so we can talk about that.",{},{}
