9224,IssuesEvent,2018-05-07 13:07:12+00:00,96581030,census-instrumentation/opencensus-python,37292253,vincent-rondot,26944525,census-instrumentation,closed,Stackdriver exporter uses an invalid format for SpanId (and parentSpanId).,[],[],7,"The V2 of Stackdriver API uses the following format for the SpanId:
""[SPAN_ID] is a unique identifier for a span within a trace; it is a 16-character hexadecimal encoding of an 8-byte array.""
(https://cloud.google.com/trace/docs/reference/v2/rest/v2/projects.traces/batchWrite#Span)
But it seems the library is still using the format of the previous version (64-bit integer).

The impact of this issue is that if the trace is distributed among different services(potentially using different languages) communicating for ex via HTTP, the HTTP Trace context Propagator will properly decode/encode the spanId/parentSpanID, but the python library will send to stackdriver an invalid SpanId/parentSpanId, and and the chain of spans of the trace will be broken (since the ID of the span and parentSpanId will be wrong).

Note that this issue is not visible if the trace is limited to a single service.

See PR with a suggestion of the fix.

Thanks,
Rgds,
Vincent


",{},{}
